Single Middle-aged male: (Mark, age 45)

Mark is a project manager at a furniture manufacturing company who works full-time and manages multiple responsibilities. 
He earns a stable salary but feels like he doesn’t always have a clear picture of where his money goes each month. 
Between mortgage payments, utilities, groceries, insurance, subscriptions, and occasional travel, his expenses add up quickly. 
He currently uses a basic spreadsheet but finds it time-consuming and difficult to visualize trends.

Mark is comfortable with business software and data dashboards, but he does not want to manually build a complex dashboard
and would prefer to have as little input as possible for initial setup, without compromising security. 

Major goals:
- Wants the software to be clean and free of clutter, ensuring he can check in on his finances during his busy workday
